name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Pembridge","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Pembridge (Herefs), which is recorded as  <i>Penebrug(g)e</i> from the 11th to 14th centuries. The place-name derives from an Old English personal name * <i>Pena</i> + Old English  <i>brycg</i> ‘bridge’. In some cases the surname may be from Pen Bridge in Shipley (Sussex), which derives from an uncertain first element + Old English  <i>brycg</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Pember","meanings":["English: perhaps a variant of <b>Pamber</b>, a habitational name from a place in Hampshire named Pamber, from Old English <i>penn</i> ‘fold, enclosure’ + <i>beorg</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":27,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":36,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Pembridge I was born about 1188, in Pembridge, Herefordshire, England, his father, Richard de Pembrugge, was 55 and his mother, Pertonilla de Cantelou de Pembrugge, was 26. He had at least 1 son with Isabel de Cantelowe. He died before 1245, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1188–before 1245":"umbes 1188–enne 1245","1188–1245":"1188–1245","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1195–1224":"1195–1224","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","1134–1190":"1134–1190","1164–Female":"1164–Surnud","1228":"1228","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1224":"1224","before 1245":"enne 1245","1245":"1245","1134":"1134","1188":"1188","1164":"1164","1195":"1195","about 1188":"umbes 1188","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Pembridge, Herefordshire, England":"Pembridge, Herefordshire, England","Pembridge, Herefordshire, England":"Pembridge, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1188–before 1245":"noin 1188–ennen vuotta 1245","1188–1245":"1188–1245","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1195–1224":"1195–1224","1228–Male":"1228–Kuollut","1134–1190":"1134–1190","1164–Female":"1164–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","about 1190":"noin 1190","1224":"1224","before 1245":"ennen vuotta 1245","1245":"1245","1134":"1134","1188":"1188","1164":"1164","1195":"1195","about 1188":"noin 118